elf and its liberation and the realising of its true nature.","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20668,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":23,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"यथाऽऽत्मतन्त्रो भगवान् विक्रीडत्यात्ममायया ।","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20669,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":23,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"विसृज्य वा यथा मायामुदास्ते साक्षिवद् विभु: ॥२३॥","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20782,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":23,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"यथा-आत्म-तन्त्र: भगवान्","text2":"In what manner, self dependent Lord","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20783,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":23,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"विक्रीडति-आत्म-मायया","text2":"sports with His own Maayaa","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20784,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":23,"lineNumber":3,"text1":"विसृज्य वा यथा मायाम्-","text2":"abandoning or how the Maayaa","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20785,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":23,"lineNumber":4,"text1":"उत्-आस्ते साक्षि-वत् विभु: ","text2":"indeed, stands witness like the All-pervading ","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20835,"chapterId":34,"type":"6-E","number":23,"lineNumber":0,"text1":"In what manner does The Lord, who is self dependent, sport with his own Maayaa? Later, abondoning His Maayaa, how does The All-pervading Lord just stand as an unconcerned witness?","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20670,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":24,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"सर्वमेतच्च भगवन् पृच्छते मेऽनुपूर्वश: ।","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20671,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":24,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"तत्त्वतोऽर्हस्युदाहर्तुं प्रपन्नाय महामुने ॥२४॥","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20786,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":24,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"सर्वम्-एतत्-च भगवन् ","text2":"all this and, O great One!","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20787,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":24,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"पृच्छते मे-अनुपूर्वश: ","text2":"asking (as I) am, one after the other","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20788,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":24,"lineNumber":3,"text1":"तत्-तु-अत:-अर्हसि-उदाहर्तुम्","text2":"that, indeed, so, are capable of expounding","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20789,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":24,"lineNumber":4,"text1":"प्रपन्नाय महामुने ","text2":"to the surrendered, (me), O holy sage!","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20836,"chapterId":34,"type":"6-E","number":24,"lineNumber":0,"text1":"O great and holy sage! I seek refuge in you, as I ask these questions. Please answer them one after the other as you are capable of doing so.","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20672,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":25,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"अत्र प्रमाणं हि भवान् परमेष्ठी यथाऽऽत्मभू: ।","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20673,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":25,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"परे चेहानुतिष्ठन्ति पूर्वेषां पूर्वजै: कृतम् ॥२५॥","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20790,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":25,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"अत्र प्रमाणम् हि भवान्","text2":"here, authority indeed are you","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20791,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":25,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"परमेष्ठी यथा-आत्म-भू: ","text2":"Brahmaa, like the self born","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20792,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":25,"lineNumber":3,"text1":"परे च-इह-अनुतिष्ठन्ति ","text2":"others and here follow ","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20793,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":25,"lineNumber":4,"text1":"पूर्वेषाम् पूर्वजै: कृतम् ","text2":"the others, by the ancestors done","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20837,"chapterId":34,"type":"6-E","number":25,"lineNumber":0,"text1":"Here, in this matter you indeed are the authority just as the self -born Brahmaa. In this world, the others merely follow the doings of the ancestors.","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20674,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":26,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"न मेऽसव: परायन्ति ब्रह्मन्ननशनादमी ।","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20675,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":26,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"पिबतोऽच्युतपीयूषमन्यत्र कुपिताद् द्विजात् ॥२६॥","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20794,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":26,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"न मे-असव: परायन्ति","text2":"not my life will leave","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20795,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":26,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"ब्रह्मन्-अनशनात्-अमी","text2":"O Sage! by not eating, this","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20796,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":26,"lineNumber":3,"text1":"पिबत:-अच्युत-पीयूषम्-","text2":"drinking Krishna's (stories') nectar, ","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20797,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":26,"lineNumber":4,"text1":"अन्यत्र कुपितात् द्विजात् ","text2":"other than enraged Braahmana's (curse)","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20838,"chapterId":34,"type":"6-E","number":26,"lineNumber":0,"text1":"O Sage! This life of mine is not going to depart by my not eating food, as I am drinking the nectar of the stories of Krishna, except for the curse of the enraged Braahmana.","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20622,"chapterId":34,"type":"3-PS","number":27,"lineNumber":0,"text1":"सूत उवाच -","text2":"Soota said -","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20676,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":27,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"स उपामन्त्रितो राज्ञा कथयामिति सत्पते: ।","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20677,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":27,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"ब्रह्मरातो भृशं प्रीतो विष्णुरातेन संसदि ॥२७॥","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20798,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":27,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"स: उपामन्त्रित: राज्ञा ","text2":"he invited by the king (Pareekshit)","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20799,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":27,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"कथयाम्-इति सत्पते: ","text2":"in the stories these of Krishna","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20800,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":27,"lineNumber":3,"text1":"ब्रह्मरात: भृशम् प्रीत:","text2":"Shukadeva, highly pleased","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20801,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":27,"lineNumber":4,"text1":"विष्णुरातेन संसदि","text2":"by Pareekshit, in the assembly","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20839,"chapterId":34,"type":"6-E","number":27,"lineNumber":0,"text1":"Shukadeva was highly pleased when he was invited to narrate the stories of Krishna, by the king Pareekshita, in the assembly.","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20678,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":28,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"प्राह भागवतं नाम पुराणं ब्रह्मसम्मितम् ।","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20679,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":28,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"ब्रह्मणे भगवत्प्रोक्तं ब्रह्मकल्प उपागते ॥२८॥","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20802,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":28,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"प्राह ","text2":"expounded","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20803,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":28,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"भागवतम् नाम पुराणम्","text2":"Bhaagavatam named Puraana","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20804,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":28,"lineNumber":3,"text1":"ब्रह्म-सम्मितम् ","text2":"Veda equal to","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20805,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":28,"lineNumber":4,"text1":"ब्रह्मणे ","text2":"To Brahmaa","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20806,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":28,"lineNumber":5,"text1":"भगवत्-प्रोक्तम् ","text2":"by The Lord said","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20807,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":28,"lineNumber":6,"text1":"ब्रह्म-कल्पे","text2":"in the Brahma Kalpa","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20808,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":28,"lineNumber":7,"text1":"उपागते ","text2":"beginning","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20840,"chapterId":34,"type":"6-E","number":28,"lineNumber":0,"text1":"He expounded the Puraana named Bhaagavatam, which was told to Brahmaa by The Lord Himself at the beginning of the Brahma Kalpa and which is as esteemed as the Vedas.","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20680,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":29,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"यद् यत् परीक्षिदृषभ: पाण्डूनामनुपृच्छति ।","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20681,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":29,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"आनुपूर्व्येण तत्सर्वमाख्यातुमुपचक्रमे ॥२९॥","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20809,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":29,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"यत् यत् परीक्षित्-ऋषभ:","text2":"all that, Pareekshita, the scion","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20810,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":29,"lineNumber":2,"text1":"पाण्डूनाम्-अनुपृच्छति","text2":"of the Paandavas, as asked","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20811,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":29,"lineNumber":3,"text1":"आनुपूर्व्येण तत्-सर्वम्-","text2":"serially, that all","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20812,"chapterId":34,"type":"5-B","number":29,"lineNumber":4,"text1":"आख्यातुम्-उपचक्रमे","text2":"to speak proceeded","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20841,"chapterId":34,"type":"6-E","number":29,"lineNumber":0,"text1":"He proceeded to speak serially of all that Pareekshit, the scion of the Paandavas' had asked.","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20682,"chapterId":34,"type":"4-S","number":30,"lineNumber":1,"text1":"इति श्रीमद्भागवते महापुराणे पारमहंस्यां संहितायां द्वितीयस्कन्धेप्रश्नविधिर्नाम् आष्टम: अध्याय: ॥८॥","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null},{"id":20842,"chapterId":34,"type":"6-E","number":30,"lineNumber":0,"text1":"Thus ends the eighth discourse entitled 'A Statement of Questions' in Book Two of the great and glorious Bhaagavata-Puraana.","text2":"","created_at":null,"updated_at":null}]